Properties.femaleVariant: [en_us]Okay, people! We're closed for the day.
[en_us]Better think twice before you answer, Alex.
[en_us]Seven years... Seven fucking years in this shithole!
[en_us]Got some nerve to show your face here, you son of a bitch.
[en_us]Give us a minute. I'll take care of this.
[en_us]Aren't you afraid that someone will see you and learn what real Alex looks like?
[en_us]We have an agent MIA in the Zone.
[en_us]You're not afraid that you'll be made?
[en_us]Fuck it. Nobody who's anybody cares about
[en_us]Krausser's soldiers are holed up in the Combat Tower, and most of those wandering the streets are riff raff.
[en_us]Krausser doesn't give a shit about me, same as the FIA... No point in using these masks anymore, if you ask me.
[en_us]You want me to stand between rock and a hard place.
[en_us]Ugh. Fine. When should I expect you there?
[en_us]I was her lead agent back in the day.
[en_us]Not her dream assignment, I take it?
[en_us]She grew up in the Metroplex ghetto. The FIA job was her ticket outta there.
[en_us]You're on the short list of people we don't serve here.
[en_us]I'll have a gin and tonic, then.
[en_us]Does that apply to me as well?
[en_us]Oh yeah? Give me back my gun, then.
[en_us]As soon as we know where we're at.
[en_us]Wouldn't be so sure of that. Not when he's in play.
[en_us]Look. I don't care what happened between you two.
[en_us]You two have unfinished business, I get that.
[en_us]We're planning an operation. Need you in the field.
[en_us]Last time I was in the field with him, I ended up in purgatory for seven years.
[en_us]We got orders from the president. It's the only thing you should care about.
[en_us]Shouldn't throw your life away because of that.
[en_us]I care about loyalty, too. And loyalty is a two-way street.
[en_us]We're coming down that street to square things with you. This is your chance to get out of here.
[en_us]No, an eye-opener. You can leave this chapter of your life behind once and for all. Let's talk.
[en_us]An agent went missing. Reed and I have to find her.
[en_us]And the FIA remembered Alex existed all of a sudden?
[en_us]And I need to finish my cig in peace.
[en_us]You're making demands? Forgot you're still an agent? It's your job.
[en_us]They forgot about it for seven fucking years. Might as well be dead for all they care.
[en_us]Tell him to give me back the time I wasted here.
[en_us]This mission is handled personally by Myers.
[en_us]She definitely didn't handle me. You want my help? Let's strike a deal.
[en_us]A retirement plan fit for an elite spy. In, say, Monaco.
[en_us]I want a gilded Herrera to show off at the Riviera and to hang out on a yacht with a fucking duchess, drinking champagne. You getting all that?
[en_us]Reed will take you to Monaco himself if that's what you want.
[en_us]Myers wants to retrieve her asset no matter the cost.
[en_us]Do you really want to get out of here? Consider this your best and only chance.
[en_us]State your terms. What do you really want?
[en_us]Just say what you want and let's be done with it.
[en_us]Fine. You can go back inside and tell him I'll do it.
[en_us]I need a bit more nicotine in my bloodstream.
[en_us][Sit] She'll agree if you  dance on the bar for her.
[en_us]So why did you come to me, Reed? After all this time?
[en_us]You've been in the Zone since the War. You know the people, the places and the rules.
[en_us]And I believe in you. Always have.
[en_us]V didn't catch you up to speed?
[en_us]But he's your friend. An old friend.
[en_us]Everyone in the zone has. Myers was on board?
[en_us]So Mi... And that's supposed to melt my sentimental heart? You think I'll help you for old time's sake? Get outta here.
[en_us]She gave Myers meeting coordinates, but never showed.
[en_us]Her brain may be fried for all we know.
[en_us]She was hacking a prototype Militech tank and something went wrong.
[en_us]Something happened while hacking. Might have fried her brain for all we know.
[en_us]Suddenly, we lost comms and she was... gone.
[en_us]So the contact broke off while she was jacked in?
[en_us]Okay. So we need someone who moves around the cyberspace a lot. News travel differently there.
[en_us]Do you have anyone specific in mind?
[en_us]You think he'll be willing to help us?
[en_us]He wanted to replace his optics. We swapped the ripperdoc for one of our guys. Slider came out blind.
[en_us]Left a little memento in his head, too. One he can never remove.
[en_us]He was our asset until he went rogue one day. But I have a good idea where to find him.
[en_us]He joined the local Haitians. Created a real community for his people. But he's still a Voodoo Boy who doesn't like company, especially the unwanted kind.
[en_us]You know where Slider is even though he went rogue?
[en_us]Oh, I don't know. No recources or incentive to go after him, maybe?
[en_us]Dealing with Slider is a conversation for another day.
[en_us]I'll meet you there. Alex and I have some catching up to do.
[en_us]I'll send you the location of Slider's hideout.
[en_us]Let me know when you reach it.
[en_us]K. Just don't kill each other, okay?
[en_us]Not in a mood for booze. NiCola, maybe?
[en_us]I did. Guess who's not here, though?
[en_us]Yeah, yeah. I'll be there in a sec. Do yuo have the coin Myers gave you?
[en_us]She's convinced I sold out to Arasaka seven years ago. It's possible it will be... tense.
[en_us][Sit] Told her you'd do anything for her.
[en_us][Sit] She'll either help us or rot here.
[en_us]Told her you were desperate and you would agree to... well, pretty much anything.
[en_us]She still cares about both you and Songbird.
could be a whole damn lot.
[en_us][db_db]DEBUG The window shutters start rolling down
[en_us]We need to prove to Alex we're there on Myers' orders.
[en_us]She's convinced they made her stay in the Zone after the war because of my betrayal.
[en_us]Taken away from me! Just like that!
[en_us]I told you to shut your mouth. I'm not talking to you yet.
[en_us]If you don't give two shits about old friends and your duty, maybe money will do the trick?
[en_us]I think you care about So Mi.
[en_us]Yeah. I think you care about So Mi and Reed more than you care to admit.
[en_us]You saw Reed. The man's desperate. He'll agree to anything at this point.
[en_us]Just say what you want in return.
[en_us]Myers can make that happen in the blink of an eye. You know that.
[en_us]Is that what you want? Just give me a number.
[en_us]A bunch of eddies ain't gonna solve it.
[en_us]Sure. Good to know where we're at.
[en_us]Fine. If that's what you need to feel better about this...
[en_us]Say I do. Still not enough to convince me to help you.
[en_us]That she'll help us if you dance for her on the bar. Butt naked.
[en_us]She wants to retire in some tax haven after this. With a nice pension plan.
[en_us]You are desperate, though. Can't say otherwise.
[en_us]No... Maybe... Definitely didn't think she'd open up like that to a stranger.
[en_us]Not me I didn't. You did. Or Myers. Either way.
[en_us]She'll do anything to get out of here.
[en_us]I know. But there's only so much a person can bend before they break. What did she say?
[en_us]You better. Otherwise she'll never trust you again.
[en_us]She believes Myers will grant her wish.
[en_us]Glad to hear I didn't promise things you couldn't deliver.
[en_us]I know about the crashed bird. And that So Mi was on board.
[en_us][GT]I don't know what to do next. What about her?
[en_us]They got me beat. I thought it's over. But then Trauma Team got there.
[en_us]I was lying in a hospital bed with a gun under my pillow, waiting for Arasaka hitmen.
[en_us]Enough with the sappy war stories. What I really wanna know is why you left me here.
[en_us]There were no hitmen. Instead, one of Myers' men showed up, carrying a suitcase full of FIA and NUSA secrets.
[en_us]Cold, obviously.. Cases that were years old, discontinued projects, names of flatlined agents.
[en_us]So... They told you to take one for the team?
[en_us]Yeah. Play the traitor and become a sleeper.
[en_us]How did I end up here though, Reed? And why?
[en_us]That was my last request to the higher-ups.
[en_us]Because the only way agents left Night City back then was in a body bag.
[en_us]So what? I should thank you now? For sending me to purgatory for seven years?
[en_us]That's seven more than other agents got.
[en_us]I can never forgive you for this, you get that?
[en_us]Have you been in touch with the others?
[en_us]What do you think? Can't talk to the dead.
[en_us]Do not let me down, Reed. If we're gonna work together again... Just don't. I won't last another year here.
[en_us][db_db]Alex taps hardly on the bar with a hand
[en_us][db_db]Alex shuts him up, she is still not talking to him
